        <updateDate>2021-07-06T15:46:38Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Access to Credit for Small Businesses Impacted by the COVID-19 Crisis Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill temporarily provides credit unions with an exception to limits on outstanding member business loans. Specifically, a loan does not count towards this limit if (1) it is used for recovery from the COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) emergency, (2) it is made by an insured credit union that has received a specified soundness rating, (3) it is made during a specified time period, and (4) it does not threaten the safety and soundness of the insured credit union. </p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
